<section class="card" id="gameInfoSection" aria-labelledby="gameInfoTitle">
  <h2 id="gameInfoTitle">Game Info</h2>

  <h3>Welcome to the News Ranker!</h3>

  <h3>Quick Guide</h3>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Pick a Topic</strong><br>
        Choose what kind of headlines you want to see.</li><br>
    <li><strong>Rank the Headline</strong><br>
        Select from 5 categories:
        <ul>
          <li>Strongly Pro</li>
          <li>Moderately Pro</li>
          <li>Neutral</li>
          <li>Moderately Anti</li>
          <li>Strongly Anti</li><br>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>See Results Instantly</strong><br>
        Right after you vote, you will see how others ranked the same headline.</li>
  </ol>

  <div class="notice-neon" role="note" style="max-width: 90%;">
    When ranking, focus on the <em>headline itself</em> - not your personal opinion about the topic.<br>
    Ask yourself: "Does this headline sound strongly pro-topic, strongly anti-topic, or more neutral in tone?"<br>
    Your task is to classify how the headline is <em>framing</em> the topic, not whether you personally agree or disagree.
  </div>

  <h3>Scoring Rules for News Ranker</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Match the Crowd Exactly:</strong> If your ranking matches the top ranking (the category with the most votes), you get <strong>+20</strong> points (Great Minds Think Alike).</li>

    <li><strong>Directionally in Line:</strong> If you do not match exactly, but your choice is in the same direction as the top ranking (for example, you chose Moderately Pro while most chose Strongly Pro), you get <strong>+10</strong> points (Directionally in Line with the Crowd).</li>

    <li><strong>Directionally Opposite:</strong> If your choice is in the opposite direction of the top ranking (counting both options in that direction), you get <strong>-10</strong> points (Swimming with Salmon).</li>

    <li><strong>Neutral Matches Neutral:</strong> If you chose Neutral and Neutral is the top ranking, you get <strong>+2</strong> points.</li>

    <li><strong>Neutral vs Non-Neutral Crowd:</strong> If you chose Neutral but the leading votes (combining both options in a direction) are not Neutral, you get <strong>-10</strong> points (Neutral where there is Nuance?).</li>

    <li><strong>Ultra Impactful Vote Bonus:</strong> If your vote flips the top category to your chosen category (any category other than Neutral), you get <strong>+50</strong> points.</li>

    <li><strong>Neutral Flip Penalty:</strong> If your vote flips the top category to Neutral, you get <strong>-30</strong> points (Numbing the Crowd to Overlook Nuance?).</li>

    <li><strong>Early Trendsetter:</strong> If a headline has fewer than 7 total votes, none of the above apply - your vote gets you <strong>+2</strong> points.</li>
  </ul>

